[
  {
    "id": "conv_db_migration_2wks_ago",
    "title": "Database migration: PostgreSQL vs MongoDB",
    "create_time": 1710000000.0,
    "update_time": 1710086400.0,
    "mapping": {
      "root_db_1": {
        "id": "root_db_1",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_db_1",
          "author": {"role": "user"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["We're planning to migrate from MongoDB to PostgreSQL for our analytics database. What are the key trade-offs we should consider?"]},
          "create_time": 1710000000.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": null,
        "children": ["node_db_2"]
      },
      "node_db_2": {
        "id": "node_db_2",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_db_2",
          "author": {"role": "assistant"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["Great question. Here are the key trade-offs:\n\nPostgreSQL:\n+ ACID transactions, data integrity\n+ Rich query language (complex JOINs)\n+ Better for structured data\n- Requires schema design upfront\n- Vertical scaling limitations\n\nMongoDB:\n+ Flexible schema, rapid iteration\n+ Horizontal scaling (sharding)\n+ Document-oriented (JSON-like)\n- Weaker transaction guarantees\n- Higher storage overhead\n\nFor analytics with relational data, PostgreSQL is typically better."]},
          "create_time": 1710000100.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": "root_db_1",
        "children": ["node_db_3"]
      },
      "node_db_3": {
        "id": "node_db_3",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_db_3",
          "author": {"role": "user"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["We have about 50GB of data. How long would migration take? Any gotchas with JSONB columns?"]},
          "create_time": 1710000200.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": "node_db_2",
        "children": ["node_db_4"]
      },
      "node_db_4": {
        "id": "node_db_4",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_db_4",
          "author": {"role": "assistant"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["50GB is manageable. Timeline depends on:\n\nFactors:\n- Network bandwidth (1-5 hours typical for 50GB)\n- Downtime tolerance (can do zero-downtime with dual-write)\n- Data transformation complexity\n\nJSONB column gotchas:\n- Indexes on nested fields add storage\n- Queries slower than normalized tables\n- Consider denormalizing frequently-accessed paths\n- Use GIN indexes for nested JSON queries\n\nRecommended approach: dual-write for 2 weeks, validate, cut over."]},
          "create_time": 1710000300.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": "node_db_3",
        "children": ["node_db_5"]
      },
      "node_db_5": {
        "id": "node_db_5",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_db_5",
          "author": {"role": "user"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["Perfect. We'll go PostgreSQL with JSONB for flexibilty on the analytics side. Thanks."]},
          "create_time": 1710000400.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": "node_db_4",
        "children": []
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "conv_api_design",
    "title": "API design: REST vs GraphQL",
    "create_time": 1710259200.0,
    "update_time": 1710345600.0,
    "mapping": {
      "root_api_1": {
        "id": "root_api_1",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_api_1",
          "author": {"role": "user"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["We're starting a new API for mobile clients. Should we use REST or GraphQL?"]},
          "create_time": 1710259200.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": null,
        "children": ["node_api_2"]
      },
      "node_api_2": {
        "id": "node_api_2",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_api_2",
          "author": {"role": "assistant"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["REST vs GraphQL depends on your use case:\n\nREST:\n+ Simpler to cache (HTTP caching)\n+ Easier monitoring/debugging\n+ Better for CRUD operations\n+ Mature tooling\n- Over/under fetching\n\nGraphQL:\n+ Query exactly what you need\n+ Single endpoint\n+ Great for mobile (bandwidth)\n- N+1 query problem\n- Caching is harder\n- Steeper learning curve\n\nFor mobile, GraphQL excels if you have many different client types (iOS, Android, web)."]},
          "create_time": 1710259300.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": "root_api_1",
        "children": ["node_api_3"]
      },
      "node_api_3": {
        "id": "node_api_3",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_api_3",
          "author": {"role": "user"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["We have iOS, Android, and web. I think GraphQL is the way. Any recommended libraries?"]},
          "create_time": 1710259400.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": "node_api_2",
        "children": ["node_api_4"]
      },
      "node_api_4": {
        "id": "node_api_4",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_api_4",
          "author": {"role": "assistant"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["For GraphQL, popular choices:\n\nBackend:\n- Apollo Server (Node.js)\n- Graphene (Python)\n- Strawberry (Python, modern)\n\nClient:\n- Apollo Client (all platforms)\n- Relay (if you need sophisticated caching)\n- urql (lighter weight)\n\nI'd recommend Apollo Server + Apollo Client for the ecosystem and community."]},
          "create_time": 1710259500.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": "node_api_3",
        "children": []
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "conv_deployment_kubernetes",
    "title": "Deployment strategy: Docker and Kubernetes",
    "create_time": 1710432000.0,
    "update_time": 1710518400.0,
    "mapping": {
      "root_deploy_1": {
        "id": "root_deploy_1",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_deploy_1",
          "author": {"role": "user"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["We're moving from VMs to containers. Kubernetes or managed services like ECS? We're AWS-based."]},
          "create_time": 1710432000.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": null,
        "children": ["node_deploy_2"]
      },
      "node_deploy_2": {
        "id": "node_deploy_2",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_deploy_2",
          "author": {"role": "assistant"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["On AWS, you have good options:\n\nECS (Elastic Container Service):\n+ AWS-native, minimal operational overhead\n+ Fargate serverless option\n+ Good if you're all-in on AWS\n- Less portable if you diversify\n\nEKS (Elastic Kubernetes Service):\n+ Kubernetes standard (portable)\n+ Better for multi-cloud future\n+ Rich ecosystem\n- Higher operational complexity\n- More expensive\n\nFor a growing startup, ECS/Fargate is often the right call. Simpler ops, lower cost. Switch to Kubernetes later if needed."]},
          "create_time": 1710432100.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": "root_deploy_1",
        "children": ["node_deploy_3"]
      },
      "node_deploy_3": {
        "id": "node_deploy_3",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_deploy_3",
          "author": {"role": "user"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["What about CI/CD? GitHub Actions vs CodePipeline vs Jenkins?"]},
          "create_time": 1710432200.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": "node_deploy_2",
        "children": ["node_deploy_4"]
      },
      "node_deploy_4": {
        "id": "node_deploy_4",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_deploy_4",
          "author": {"role": "assistant"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["GitHub Actions is best for GitHub-hosted repos. It's tightly integrated, zero-config for pushes. CodePipeline if you want deep AWS integration. Jenkins if you need self-hosted with full control. I'd recommend GitHub Actions for speed and simplicity."]},
          "create_time": 1710432300.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": "node_deploy_3",
        "children": []
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "conv_debugging_session",
    "title": "Debugging: Memory leak in production",
    "create_time": 1710604800.0,
    "update_time": 1710691200.0,
    "mapping": {
      "root_bug_1": {
        "id": "root_bug_1",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_bug_1",
          "author": {"role": "user"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["Our Node.js service is leaking memory in production. Memory grows ~50MB/hour. Where do I start debugging?"]},
          "create_time": 1710604800.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": null,
        "children": ["node_bug_2"]
      },
      "node_bug_2": {
        "id": "node_bug_2",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_bug_2",
          "author": {"role": "assistant"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["Memory leak debugging steps:\n\n1. Enable heap snapshots: `--inspect` flag\n2. Use Chrome DevTools or clinic.js\n3. Take snapshots every hour, compare\n4. Look for growing object counts\n5. Check for:\n   - Event listeners not unsubscribed\n   - Circular references in caches\n   - Timers not cleared\n   - Unclosed database connections\n\nMost common: event listeners and caches. Start there."]},
          "create_time": 1710604900.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": "root_bug_1",
        "children": ["node_bug_3"]
      },
      "node_bug_3": {
        "id": "node_bug_3",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_bug_3",
          "author": {"role": "user"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["Found it! We were accumulating event listeners in a WebSocket handler. Fixed by adding removeListener. Memory now stable."]},
          "create_time": 1710605000.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": "node_bug_2",
        "children": []
      }
    }
  },
