  {
    "id": "conv_testing_strategy",
    "title": "Testing strategy and coverage",
    "create_time": 1710864000.0,
    "update_time": 1710950400.0,
    "mapping": {
      "root_test_1": {
        "id": "root_test_1",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_test_1",
          "author": {"role": "user"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["What's a good testing strategy? Unit, integration, e2e? We're not sure where to focus effort."]},
          "create_time": 1710864000.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": null,
        "children": ["node_test_2"]
      },
      "node_test_2": {
        "id": "node_test_2",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_test_2",
          "author": {"role": "assistant"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["Pyramid approach:\n\nUnit (60%):\n- Fast, isolated\n- Business logic, helpers\n- Target 80%+ coverage\n\nIntegration (30%):\n- API routes, database\n- Mock external services\n- Test happy path + error cases\n\nE2E (10%):\n- Critical user flows only\n- Selenium/Cypress\n- Slow, avoid redundancy\n\nDon't aim for 100% coverage. Focus on high-value paths."]},
          "create_time": 1710864100.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": "root_test_1",
        "children": ["node_test_3"]
      },
      "node_test_3": {
        "id": "node_test_3",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_test_3",
          "author": {"role": "user"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["Clear breakdown. We'll start with unit tests and integration for the API. E2E can come later."]},
          "create_time": 1710950400.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": "node_test_2",
        "children": []
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "conv_scaling_concerns",
    "title": "Scaling to 1M users",
    "create_time": 1710518400.0,
    "update_time": 1710604800.0,
    "mapping": {
      "root_scale_1": {
        "id": "root_scale_1",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_scale_1",
          "author": {"role": "user"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["We're approaching 100K users. What architectural changes do we need for 1M?"]},
          "create_time": 1710518400.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": null,
        "children": ["node_scale_2"]
      },
      "node_scale_2": {
        "id": "node_scale_2",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_scale_2",
          "author": {"role": "assistant"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["100K to 1M requires architectural shifts:\n\nDatabase:\n- Horizontal sharding (user_id % N)\n- Read replicas\n- Caching layer (Redis)\n\nAPI:\n- Load balancing\n- Rate limiting\n- CDN for static assets\n\nOps:\n- Monitoring/alerting\n- Auto-scaling\n- Disaster recovery\n\nStart with caching and read replicas. Sharding is painful, delay if possible."]},
          "create_time": 1710518500.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": "root_scale_1",
        "children": ["node_scale_3"]
      },
      "node_scale_3": {
        "id": "node_scale_3",
        "message": {
          "id": "msg_scale_3",
          "author": {"role": "user"},
          "content": {"content_type": "text", "parts": ["Should we start sharding now or wait? We're still monolithic."]},
          "create_time": 1710604800.0,
          "metadata": {}
        },
        "parent": "node_scale_2",
        "children": []
      }
    }
  },
